abstract: Senator Elizabeth Warren and Mayor Pete Buttigieg increasingly are gaining momentum ahead of the February Iowa caucuses.
snippet: Senator Elizabeth Warren and Mayor Pete Buttigieg increasingly are gaining momentum ahead of the February Iowa caucuses.
lead_paragraph: CEDAR RAPIDS, Iowa — For months, the presidential race in Iowa was a contest between two titans of the Democratic political world, each representing distinct poles of a party struggling to define its identity in the Trump era.

abstract: Forget Scandinavia. Switzerland is richer and yet has a surprisingly equal wealth distribution.
snippet: Forget Scandinavia. Switzerland is richer and yet has a surprisingly equal wealth distribution.
lead_paragraph: Like many progressive intellectuals, Bernie Sanders traces his vision of economic paradise not to socialist dictatorships like Venezuela but to their distant cousins in Scandinavia, which are just as wealthy and democratic as the United States but have more equitable distributions of wealth, as well as affordable health care and free college for all.

abstract: A ‘Medicare for all’ proposal would push the boundaries of taxing corporations and the rich to fund expanded government programs.
snippet: A ‘Medicare for all’ proposal would push the boundaries of taxing corporations and the rich to fund expanded government programs.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Three years after President Trump rode a wave of populist anger into office, some of his top Democratic challengers are calling for a fundamental reordering of American capitalism, arguing that voters will embrace bold plans to reverse decades of rising inequality by raising taxes on corporations and the rich.

headline_print_headline: Trillion-Dollar Pledges Cement Democrats’ Bet on Taxing Rich

abstract: What we know: Elizabeth Warren has seized much of Bernie Sanders’ youthful following, and her coalition transcends divisions over policy. What we don’t know: A lot, still.
snippet: What we know: Elizabeth Warren has seized much of Bernie Sanders’ youthful following, and her coalition transcends divisions over policy. What we don’t know: A lot, still.
lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren is starting to stand out in Iowa, as Friday’s New York Times/Siena College poll shows. But she isn’t standing alone — at least not yet.

abstract: In a legislative district in southern New Jersey, the polarizing national battle over impeachment is playing out in real time.

abstract: Ms. Warren said “complacency does not win elections,” as she pushed for big changes, while moderates like Pete Buttigieg and Joe Biden vowed they could unite the country.
snippet: Ms. Warren said “complacency does not win elections,” as she pushed for big changes, while moderates like Pete Buttigieg and Joe Biden vowed they could unite the country.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Displaying a new assertiveness toward her Democratic opponents, Elizabeth Warren laced into her chief political rivals, warning on Friday night that the country was in a “time of crisis” and arguing that Democrats would lose in 2020 if they nominated “anyone who comes on this stage and tells you they can make change without a fight.”

abstract: Ms. Warren would impose huge tax increases on businesses and billionaires to pay for “Medicare for all,” but she said she would not raise taxes on the middle class.
snippet: Ms. Warren would impose huge tax increases on businesses and billionaires to pay for “Medicare for all,” but she said she would not raise taxes on the middle class.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Elizabeth Warren on Friday revealed her plan to pay for an expansive transformation of the nation’s health care system, proposing huge tax increases on businesses and wealthy Americans to help cover $20.5 trillion in new federal spending.
